    a: "The diagnostic-level read is still free for one entity. Multi-entity or multi-year files genuinely take longer to assess accurately, and may need a paid deep diagnostic before a fixed-fee scope is honest &mdash; typically a flat fee credited toward the engagement if you proceed. We&rsquo;ll tell you <em>before</em> the meter starts, on the discovery call, and you can stop there at no cost."
  - q: "Is the written fixed-fee scope binding?"
    a: "The scope binds us to the fee and the deliverables; it doesn&rsquo;t bind you. You can sit on it, take it to a different firm, or pass entirely. If you proceed, the fee in the scope is the fee we charge &mdash; no scope creep, no hourly upcharges, no &lsquo;we found more, here&rsquo;s a change order.&rsquo; If genuinely new in-scope work emerges mid-engagement, we re-quote in writing before any of it happens."
  - q: "Who actually reviews the file?"
    a: "A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor &mdash; typically our lead practice for the diagnostic itself. If the engagement after the review is best matched to a vetted local operator like Westgate Financial Services in Texas, we&rsquo;ll introduce you. The Certified ProAdvisor doing the review is the same person you talk to on the diagnostic call &mdash; never a rotating queue, never a junior offshore."
  - q: "What happens if you tell me the file is fine?"
